Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.00,0:00:23.58,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't I made everything work out all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.46,0:00:26.71,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Without me, it would've been a lot worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.71,0:00:29.21,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,All of it was because I was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.73,0:00:35.18,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You should have a greater debt to me \Nthan you could ever repay!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.94,0:00:45.23,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we stop for now?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.97,0:00:47.81,Default - flashback,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll repay all of them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.57,0:00:50.02,Default - flashback,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,And we'll end this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.86,0:00:59.80,Default - flashback,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, Julius, your good\Nnature is going to waste,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.80,0:01:02.12,Default - flashback,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,playing the villain for someone like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.48,0:01:06.45,Default - flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't the slightest idea \Nwhat you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.45,0:01:09.45,Default - flashback,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,How could you get yourself punished, \Ntrying to protect a guy like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.45,0:01:10.17,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,It's foolish!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.65,0:01:13.47,Default - flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I only acted as I wished,\Ntrue to my own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.47,0:01:16.34,Default - flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Righteously, in my own way,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.34,0:01:19.28,Default - flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,and without shame, as I wished.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.99,0:01:22.60,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.60,0:01:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old Man Wil is busy preparing, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.94,0:01:27.92,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,It was a request from our guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.92,0:01:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.71,0:01:32.11,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,If they're just practicing,\Nit's {\i1}nyo{\i0} big deal, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.59,0:01:36.78,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, it appears to me \Nhe's just making excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.32,0:01:38.03,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Excuses?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.67,0:01:42.24,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to say, "I'm just\Nfine. I'm working hard."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.17,0:01:45.50,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Can you blame him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.81,0:03:25.80,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.36,0:03:27.57,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.57,0:03:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have to apologize for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.80,0:03:34.20,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,None of this was your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.20,0:03:38.15,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,No, I am a friend to you,\Nas well as to Julius.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.81,0:03:41.71,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,My own lack of virtue was \Nresponsible for my failure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.71,0:03:44.53,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,to stop a disagreement between my two friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.86,0:03:47.98,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,That duel had no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.46,0:03:50.75,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.16,0:03:52.35,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.35,0:03:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What came of you two fighting there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.11,0:03:56.67,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,You were hurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.67,0:03:59.71,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,and Julius tarnished his own career.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:04.29,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,Why not try to have a calm, \Nopen discussion with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.75,0:04:07.10,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that will clear up the misunder—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:07.10,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Reinhard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.13,0:04:11.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I get how you feel, and I appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.66,0:04:13.36,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You really are a nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.36,0:04:13.77,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.07,0:04:16.54,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't accept that proposal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.54,0:04:17.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We're done talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.93,0:04:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.96,0:04:21.43,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.43,0:04:22.11,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.66,0:04:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you gain from that duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:26.41,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,You've only suffered losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.09,0:04:28.08,Default,Reinhard,0000,0000,0000,,Even Emilia-sama—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.08,0:04:30.28,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better head back for today, Reinhard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.96,0:04:34.25,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Before your mistress gets lonely \Nand starts yelling for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.75,0:04:43.13,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your own damn business.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.95,0:04:54.23,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we stop for now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:06.96,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,You must be tired after practice, Subaru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.14,0:05:14.89,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, you don't think I'm pathetic?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.89,0:05:16.30,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.78,0:05:18.21,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You do? Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.78,0:05:22.01,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Then why are you still here \Nwith a pathetic loser like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.01,0:05:23.26,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Because you were told to?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.65,0:05:25.32,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that I think you're pathetic
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.32,0:05:28.69,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,and my staying with you are not contradictory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.69,0:05:31.31,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, even if I had not been ordered to,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.31,0:05:32.93,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I would have stayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.17,0:05:35.39,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.55,0:05:38.35,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Because I want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.84,0:05:43.94,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go out tomorrow, Subaru-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.54,0:05:47.61,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't gone anywhere in the \Nthree days since we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.18,0:06:01.27,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,Interested in the royal selection, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.27,0:06:04.54,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! Don't sneak up on me with that face!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.54,0:06:06.37,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, where's Rem?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.32,0:06:13.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make someone without \Nexperience watch your shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.17,0:06:16.83,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,Five candidates, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.83,0:06:20.94,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,If you ask me, letting a half-elf be \None of them is pure insanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.71,0:06:23.56,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,"Emilia," eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.56,0:06:26.75,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way a relative of the \Nwitch could become our ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.75,0:06:29.11,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,They've gotta be crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.67,0:06:30.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Why does everyone say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.95,0:06:34.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't mean she has anything \Nto do with the witch!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.64,0:06:35.12,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.01,0:06:38.57,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Just because she's a half-elf, \Ndon't lump them together
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.57,0:06:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and brush her off!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.30,0:06:41.79,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:45.15,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That Emilia girl... I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.15,0:06:48.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She might really care about this \Nkingdom's people, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:50.72,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, why are you getting so worked up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.72,0:06:51.55,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.03,0:06:54.01,Default - flashback,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,It was for you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.97,0:06:57.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.16,0:06:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the Jealous Witch?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.84,0:07:01.39,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You think all half-elves are dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.39,0:07:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just because the witch was one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.94,0:07:05.32,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.93,0:07:07.40,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's scared of the witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.40,0:07:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's common knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.40,0:07:14.57,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,As long as people see her that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.57,0:07:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she can't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.93,0:07:18.76,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.22,0:07:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who would actually choose to support her?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:30.19,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,Try not to say the word "witch" \Ntoo loudly in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.19,0:07:32.18,Default,Kadomon,0000,0000,0000,,You never know who's listening, or where.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.84,0:07:42.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.11,0:07:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone felt that way about you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.03,0:07:48.73,Default - flashback,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I can't understand if you\Ndon't tell me, Subaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.70,0:07:53.11,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't understand if you\Ndon't tell me, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.92,0:08:20.05,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki Subaru, would you \Nmind joining me for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.52,0:08:22.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Crusch-san... Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.80,0:08:23.81,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.76,0:08:25.92,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.92,0:08:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time you've seen \Nme out of business attire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.20,0:08:31.99,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,The breeze is pleasantly cool tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.76,0:08:35.11,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect conditions for sharing a drink,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.11,0:08:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as we gaze upon the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.19,0:08:42.41,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't drink alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.88,0:08:45.11,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome to drink water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.11,0:08:47.75,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be drinking enough to get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.32,0:09:01.64,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,How goes the healing of your gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.82,0:09:04.69,Default - flashback,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.55,0:09:06.78,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.21,0:09:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Well, it goes, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:10.81,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.81,0:09:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Felis is excellent with healing magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.00,0:09:15.49,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,You can trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:22.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You always seem busy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.45,0:09:23.81,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,In response to a certain occurrence,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.81,0:09:28.17,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,my family is currently gathering \Npeople and objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.41,0:09:31.21,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, since word of the\Nroyal selection spread,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.21,0:09:33.54,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I've received proposals every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.54,0:09:35.47,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure the other candidates have, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.47,0:09:36.84,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,P-Proposals?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.84,0:09:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, as in marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.54,0:09:40.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.67,0:09:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess they're all single...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.30,0:09:44.22,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Does that bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.99,0:09:47.52,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.52,0:09:48.41,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.41,0:09:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wilhelm-san said he had a beautiful wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.87,0:09:58.20,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware that Wilhelm serves me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:00.83,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.38,0:10:04.83,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,What are {\i1}nyou{\i0} doing here, Subaru-{\i1}kyun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.26,0:10:06.77,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,And Crusch-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.77,0:10:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dressed so vulnerably?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.86,0:10:10.43,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Is it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no different than what \NI wear to dine with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.96,0:10:15.94,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly the problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.94,0:10:18.13,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Men are {\i1}nyo{\i0}thing but wolves!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:19.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're a man, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.35,0:10:22.48,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough joking, Felis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.48,0:10:25.60,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,All who were present at the royal selection
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.60,0:10:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,know whom Subaru loves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.14,0:10:31.06,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I heard they had a fight, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.57,0:10:35.73,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, Subaru-{\i1}kyun{\i0}, you're so easy to read!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.98,0:10:39.23,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cast your gaze down, Natsuki Subaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.23,0:10:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.20,0:10:42.98,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,When your eyes are clouded, your soul darkens.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.98,0:10:45.02,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,That means your future is closed to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.02,0:10:47.77,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,and you lose sight of your reasons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.77,0:10:50.04,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,When you do what you know to be right,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.04,0:10:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what can you do by looking downward?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.58,0:10:55.82,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Lift your head, face forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.82,0:10:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and reach out your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.38,0:11:01.76,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I do not want to regard you \Nas an insignificant enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.49,0:11:04.52,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,If Crusch-sama says so,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.52,0:11:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you have {\i1}nyo{\i0} choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.76,0:11:11.40,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,The point is, Subaru-{\i1}kyun{\i0}, you need to \Nhurry and make up with Emilia-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.40,0:11:13.54,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Think about what you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.54,0:11:17.02,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,to accomplish that, and do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.74,0:11:21.57,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What I can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:29.63,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,There is something I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:36.53,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Something that only I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.07,0:11:38.83,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.83,0:11:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't even have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.58,0:11:46.89,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,The wind is picking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.35,0:11:52.16,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,282)}It looks as if the weather will \Nbe rough again tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.08,0:12:00.19,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we stop for now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.48,0:12:02.36,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.36,0:12:05.15,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You've seen how far I've come in taking blows!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:09.16,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Your attitude seems quite\Ndifferent this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.64,0:12:13.79,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, Crusch-san gave \Nme some good advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.81,0:12:19.42,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If I just get a chance, I can make \Nany problem disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.99,0:12:24.22,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Then, let us call it a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:24.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.50,0:12:29.53,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I think teaching swordsmanship, \Nwhich will make a man stronger,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.53,0:12:34.85,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,to one who has abandoned the option \Nto get stronger seems meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.12,0:12:38.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What do you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.14,0:12:39.23,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.50,0:12:43.09,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,We must discuss something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.07,0:12:48.18,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Has Rem told you what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:50.40,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,What I felt was...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.40,0:12:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like a presence, \Nthrough the sense I share with my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.41,0:12:55.98,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,My sister could have used
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.98,0:12:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,her clairvoyance to get a \Nclearer picture, but I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.56,0:13:02.26,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,So I guess you picked up a {\i1}nya{\i0}sty sort \Nof synesthesia from her, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.81,0:13:05.32,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know the details, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.32,0:13:06.62,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,But it came from the Mathers domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.62,0:13:09.89,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,which you know as Margrave\NRoswaal's territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.89,0:13:13.77,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Evidently, some troubling movement was \Nseen in the vicinity of his mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.31,0:13:17.59,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Parts of the domain are already on high alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.59,0:13:18.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Troubling movement?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.57,0:13:22.26,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,We did foresee this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.26,0:13:27.49,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,From the moment the margrave declared \Nhis intention to back Emilia, a half-elf.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:31.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You mean there's trouble happening \Nbecause of that prejudice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.95,0:13:34.21,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,That is likely a correct summation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.08,0:13:39.18,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The moment I leave her side, this happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.18,0:13:42.37,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone around her is an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.78,0:13:44.67,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who can take her side...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:49.02,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.69,0:13:50.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.47,0:13:53.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We have to go and help, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.40,0:13:56.49,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You mustn't, Subaru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.49,0:13:58.89,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,You have to obey Emilia-sama's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.89,0:14:01.28,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,She told you to focus on healing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.28,0:14:02.82,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,And I agree!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.82,0:14:05.03,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Healing must take priority now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.92,0:14:09.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, we're the only ones
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.27,0:14:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who can take Emilia's side!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.68,0:14:16.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You heard that, Crusch-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.14,0:14:19.72,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We're going back to the mansion, \Nback to where Emilia is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.72,0:14:22.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Until it's taken care of, my healing will—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.32,0:14:22.67,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki Subaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.07,0:14:25.00,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,If you leave here,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.00,0:14:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that will make you my enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.62,0:14:31.74,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to correct one idea you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.74,0:14:35.08,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I have only allowed you to stay here \Nas a guest, receiving treatment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.08,0:14:37.26,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,because I am contracted to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.26,0:14:38.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Contracted?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.74,0:14:41.92,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia and I formed a contract
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.92,0:14:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,regarding your treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.03,0:14:44.86,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.44,0:14:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you abandon that contract yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.89,0:14:50.22,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I am not obligated to continue protecting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.22,0:14:52.27,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,The moment you leave this household,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.27,0:14:55.57,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia and I will not hesitate\Nto become enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.67,0:14:58.75,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I was wrong about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.26,0:15:03.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I thought, just maybe,\Nyou and I could get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.32,0:15:06.59,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, of course... That was just a \Nlittle joke over drinks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.28,0:15:09.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I was stupid to take you seriously
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.06,0:15:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you told me,\Nan enemy, to do what I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.48,0:15:14.83,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want me to leave \Nbecause getting Emilia
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.83,0:15:16.77,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,out of trouble will be bad for you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.42,0:15:19.53,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nyow{\i0} I think you have it all wrong—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.53,0:15:20.49,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Felis, enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.49,0:15:21.82,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,No, I will say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.82,0:15:24.40,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,The mistake he's making is a bit too grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.13,0:15:28.35,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you leave, nothing will change.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.35,0:15:29.77,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,You'd be wasting your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.77,0:15:32.05,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,After making a fool of yourself at the castle
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.05,0:15:35.41,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,and being clobbered by Julius, \N{\i1}nyou{\i0} still don't realize that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.41,0:15:39.45,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,If you stay to finish your treatment, \Nyou'll be much better off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:45.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided. I'm going back to Emilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.06,0:15:47.30,Default,Suabru,0000,0000,0000,,Though it wasn't for long, \Nthanks for taking care of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.66,0:15:49.81,Default,Felix,0000,0000,0000,,Is it {\i1}nyot{\i0} true that a good man
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.81,0:15:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,knows how to take a warning?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.76,0:15:54.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's thanks to your warning that \NI've made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.23,0:15:56.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.42,0:16:02.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, how long until we reach the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.59,0:16:04.92,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,About two and a half days, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.92,0:16:06.07,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Over two days?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.07,0:16:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It took less than half a day to get here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.03,0:16:09.08,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.08,0:16:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a fog over the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.45,0:16:12.95,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,so we need to take a detour.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.95,0:16:14.63,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about fog?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.63,0:16:16.71,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,The fog is created by the White Whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.71,0:16:18.16,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Should we encounter it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.78,0:16:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we would not survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.21,0:16:31.07,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for lending us your \Ndragon-drawn carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.07,0:16:33.78,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,In my master's stead, I offer my gratitude for
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.78,0:16:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the favor you have shown us till today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.08,0:16:38.15,Default,Wilhelm,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. Please take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.84,0:16:45.08,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Are you getting anything from Ram?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.08,0:16:49.64,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,No, our shared sense is consciously \Ncontrolled, to an extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.64,0:16:50.99,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,This morning, I think
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that what I sensed was something \Nthat exceeded my sister's control.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.77,0:17:00.09,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So Ram didn't even mean \Nto let us know about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.54,0:17:05.04,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Is she trying to keep\Nus from getting involved?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.38,0:17:08.08,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.08,0:17:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She needs me by her side...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.75,0:17:14.96,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I can save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.96,0:17:17.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Once I do, I'm sure she'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.95,0:17:19.22,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She has to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.06,0:17:35.48,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we stopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.48,0:17:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.78,0:17:38.48,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Subaru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.48,0:17:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ground dragon cannot go any farther.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.60,0:17:52.90,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.08,0:17:57.15,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kun, are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:17:58.69,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.29,0:18:08.67,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.67,0:18:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I hoped we could talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.81,0:18:13.39,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... You, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.87,0:18:15.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Can't help that, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.63,0:18:23.61,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're really worried about the mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.61,0:18:26.42,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,after what you felt through your shared sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.21,0:18:30.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.02,0:18:33.66,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We're not the sort of lovable little kids \Nto get our feelings hurt so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.66,0:18:36.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get right back, and I'll fix things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.46,0:18:42.39,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I have put all my faith\Nin you, Subaru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.50,0:18:57.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,R-Rem-san, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.02,0:18:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why are you holding on to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.66,0:19:02.34,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Because I want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.00,0:19:10.69,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I... I know this feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.12,0:19:12.92,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I am healing your gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.92,0:19:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just as Felix-sama did, Subaru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.87,0:19:17.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, healing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.68,0:19:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're healing me... Of course you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.95,0:19:25.81,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Because you want to, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.00,0:19:31.81,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She'll probably be angry with \Nme at first, won't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.41,0:19:35.84,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,If you take the time to properly face her
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.26,0:19:38.69,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,and communicate how you feel with words,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.36,0:19:41.22,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure she will understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.67,0:19:44.53,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,You are a wonderful person, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.10,0:19:47.40,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.85,0:19:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... I am, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.99,0:19:54.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia is hopeless without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.52,0:19:57.50,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Because I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.98,0:20:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,care about her... so much...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.26,0:20:11.39,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,So save just a tiny bit of that for me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.05,0:20:17.65,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go anywhere. Okay, Subaru-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.42,0:20:28.38,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, wake up! We oversle—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.29,0:20:35.38,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now! Good morni—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.69,0:20:38.59,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the blue-haired girl \Nwho was here with me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.59,0:20:41.06,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The lady you were with, u-uh—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.06,0:20:41.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't hear you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.95,0:20:45.39,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I was saying that she left during the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.39,0:20:47.62,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Here are your things...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.07,0:20:54.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.45,0:20:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you thinking, Rem?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.62,0:21:02.66,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that you would understand me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.15,0:21:08.32,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear Subaru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.02,0:21:12.01,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,When you read this letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.01,0:21:15.37,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you will be very angry with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.62,0:21:18.08,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I shall not ask
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.08,0:21:21.95,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,for your forgiveness for leaving you \Nto go to the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.23,0:21:22.92,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The one in there might agree to your offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.92,0:21:25.37,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,But please understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.37,0:21:29.55,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Bringing you to the mansion right \Nnow would be very dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.02,0:21:31.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one called Otto?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:38.77,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,So please wait here for me to return."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:38.77,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'll accept your payment, but I think \Nthis is very reckless, Natsuki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.58,0:21:48.99,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So you think I'm a useless \Ngood-for-nothing, too, Rem?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.75,0:21:54.45,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,I think I've just been introduced to \Nsomeone who could be real trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.21,0:21:58.53,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, fine. If you won't trust me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.53,0:22:00.75,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,then why should I depend on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.88,0:22:17.64,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but can we please turn back now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.06,0:22:20.62,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? After coming this far?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.62,0:22:22.89,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,My ground dragon is frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.32,0:22:26.37,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,It instinctively knows that this place \Nis too dangerous to approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.00,0:22:29.73,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.34,0:22:33.49,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,We're already in the Mathers domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.04,0:22:35.85,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,near a village called Arlam.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.85,0:22:37.12,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.50,0:22:41.54,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki-san, you can't go out there! \NLet's turn back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.54,0:22:43.72,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,This is far enough, Otto.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.19,0:22:46.30,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You can take the money and all my stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.55,0:22:47.92,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.92,0:22:49.60,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Please rethink this!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.60,0:22:50.99,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.71,0:22:58.73,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.12,0:23:03.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's too quiet...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.02,0:23:27.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.89,0:23:39.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.12,0:23:52.74,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.71,0:25:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rem...
